09/03/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A train derailed in central Greece on Saturday (March 8th) leaving 28 people injured, including three children. The train was travelling from Athens to Alexandroupolis via Thessaloniki, when at least five of its carriages derailed near the town of Larissa. Rescue teams had to break windows to reach those trapped inside the carriages. Preliminary information suggests human error may have caused the derailment. (BBC, AP, ANA-MPA, Reuters - 08/03/08)
